<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-03-13T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-03-13T20:00:00-05:00" n="63" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d63">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/483: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-03-14T09:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">March 14,
                                        1927—9 a.m.</hi></date> [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>]<lb/>[Received 9:55 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>218. My 214, March 14, 5 p.m. Following from Hankow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“March 13, noon. Ch’en sent telegraphic instructions last night
                                    to Commissioner Foreign Affairs and Political Bureau at Foochow
                                    directing that special efforts be made to adequately protect
                                    life and property Americans in that region. Price informed.”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>